sample_growth_protocol_ch1: freshly isolated cells from human Liver tissue
sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Human liver tissue was passed through 70-μm mesh filters and rinsed with 10% FBS in PBS. Leukocytes were isolated using Ficoll gradients., Illumina, SMART-seq
sample_data_processing: Single-end reads were trimmed for low quality bases and removal of low-quality reads using ReadTools, Trimmed reads were mapped to the Homo sapiens genome (GRCh38.92 assembly) using STAR (v2.5.3a) mapper, The reads mapped in multiple genomic locations were eliminated by using Samtools (v1.4), Read counts for features (exons) were generated using the featureCounts function from the Subread package (v 1.22.1), For ATAC-seq low quality peaks such as blacklisted peaks were eliminated.
supplementary_files_format_and_content: Raw gene count matrix was generated using featureCounts function from the Subread package (v 1.22.1) with Ensembl Known Gene models (version GRCh38.92) as reference annotationsATAC-seq peaks were identified by using the HOMER tool

sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Human liver tissue was passed through 70-μm mesh filters and rinsed with 10% FBS in PBS. Leukocytes were isolated using Ficoll gradients., Illumina, SMART-seq
sample_data_processing: Single-end reads were trimmed for low quality bases and removal of low-quality reads using ReadTools, Trimmed reads were mapped to the Homo sapiens genome (GRCh38.92 assembly) using STAR (v2.5.3a) mapper, The reads mapped in multiple genomic locations were eliminated by using Samtools (v1.4), Read counts for features (exons) were generated using the featureCounts function from the Subread package (v 1.22.1), For ATAC-seq low quality peaks such as blacklisted peaks were eliminated.

sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Cells were resuspended in PBS with 0.04% BSA. 20K CD45+ cells were loaded on the chromium single cell controller of 10X Genomics  as described in the manufacturers protocol and processed using the 3' scRNA-seq workflow., We followed the protocol according to the manufacturers instructions with no adaptations.
sample_data_processing: Cell Ranger (v3.0.2) mkfastq method demultiplexed raw base call (BCL) files generated by Illumina sequencers into FASTQ files., Cell Ranger (v3.0.2) count method took FASTQ files from cellranger mkfastq and performs alignment to the Homo sapiens genome (GRCh38.92 assembly), filtering, barcode counting, and UMI counting., Cell Ranger (v3.0.2) aggr method was used to aggregate the outputs from three runs of cellranger count., Downstream analysis were perfored using R package Seurat v3.02 and 10x G ...
supplementary_files_format_and_content: Gene matrix and barcode files for each donor were created by Cell Ranger (v3.0.2)
